      • EUID

        public EUID(byte[] bytes)
        Constructor for creating an EUID from an array of bytes. The array is most-significant byte first, and must not be zero length.

        If the array is smaller than BYTES, then it is effectively padded with leading bytes with the correct sign.

        If the array is longer than BYTES, then values at index BYTES and beyond are ignored.

        Parameters:
        bytes - The array of bytes to be used.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if bytes is 0 bytes in length.
        See Also:
        toByteArray()

      • routingDistanceFrom

        public int routingDistanceFrom(EUID other)
        Calculate the routing difference between this EUID and the specified EUID.

        Currently the algorithm is numberOfLeadingZeros(this ^ other).

        Parameters:
        other - The EUID for which to calculate the routing distance from.
        Returns:
        The routing distance.

      • compareDistances

        public int compareDistances(EUID first,
                            EUID second)
        Compare the distances of first and second from this, treating our unsigned 128-bit number system as a ring with values 0 and 2128-1 adjacent.

        The algorithm for calculating distance between two nodes is:

        distance = minunsigned((a - b) mod 2128, (b - a) mod 2128)
        Parameters:
        first - The first ID to calculate distance
        second - The second ID to calculate the distance
        Returns:
        0 if both distances are equal, 1 if first is further away and -1 if first is closer.
